                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_kʼæzyn" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kʼæzyn</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kʼwæzun</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>заикаться</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>stutter</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>ænækʼæzgæjæ ʒūry</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>говорит не заикаясь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>speaks without stuttering</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ænækʼæzgæjæ ʒūry</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>говорит не заикаясь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>speaks without stuttering</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Звукоподражательное. Иран. %i*kwaz-%i, и.е. %i*k˳ag-%i представляет, по-видимому, вариацию индоевропейского %i*k˳ak-%i, наличного в славянских (<mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/> <w>kvakati</w> <gloss><q>крякать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>квакать</w></mentioned> и пр.), германских (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>quacken, quaken</w> <gloss><q>квакать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>крякать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>quackeln</w> <gloss><q>тараторить</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.). Появление смычно-гортанного %ikʼ%i — как в других звукоподражательных и экспрессивных словах (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>522—533</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Onomatopoeic. Iranian %i*kwaz-%i, Indo-European %i*k˳ag-%i is apparently a variant of Indo-European %i*k˳ak-%i, which is attested in Slavic languages (<mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/> <w>kvakati</w> <gloss><q>quack</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>квакать</w> <gloss><q>croack</q></gloss></mentioned> etc.), in Germanic languages (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/> <w>quacken, quaken</w> <gloss><q>croack</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/> <gloss><q>quack</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w>quackeln</w> <gloss><q>gabble</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.). The emergence of an obstruent guttural consonant %ikʼ%i is as in other onomatopoeic and expressive words (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>522—533</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><note type="internal">хехе в примере каритив</note></entry></body></text></TEI>